Full Description: ExpertCEO is an online business community designed to meet the unique needs of senior executives by connecting them with peers who confront similar challenges and opportunities everyday. All other site visitors, including those who aspire to reach the C-suite, are able to view content across the site, offering a close-up look into the issues and challenges confronting CEOs. The entire ExpertCEO community has access to a deep repository of knowledge on critical topics like compensation, financing, board of directors relations and general business strategy. A comprehensive database of service providers assists members with the daily aspects of running a business.  ExpertCEO is complementary to traditional CEO organizations organizations like Vistage and YPO, yet ExpertCEO offers two significant advantages — scale and speed. Scale represents the number of other CEOs who are queried when a question is asked. Rather than querying a group of 10 to 12 members, participants query ExpertCEO's entire member base, thus achieving "the wisdom of the crowds." Speed is achieved by simply logging on to ask a question, rather than attending a meeting or trying to contact a network of contacts via phone or email.

Description: Operating Analytics offers OR Forecast, a product that gives surgical departments a daily forecast of operating room utilization.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Operating Analytics' product, OR Forecast, gives surgical departments a daily forecast of operating room utilization. Hospitals allocate operating room (OR) time using block scheduling—a system that dictates specific days and times during which surgeons can schedule surgeries. Block schedules often do not coincide with actual OR demand, resulting in poor resource utilization and suboptimal financial performance. As such, OR managers must navigate a unique set of resource-related challenges that are not addressed elsewhere in the hospital setting. Operating Analytics’ vision is to improve hospital management through the use of data analytics. Its first product disrupts a paradox that hospitals face: access to OR time is restricted for scheduling surgeries, while OR time frequently goes unused. The Operating Analytics system interfaces with existing scheduling products and converts stored data into actionable knowledge to support intelligent decision-making and resource allocation for ORs. While other companies perform predictive modeling, Operating Analytics positions itself as the only one that focuses on OR demand forecasting and decision support.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Health Care, Software
Founders: Rick Maher, Ryan Graue, Tejas Shah
Top 5 Investors: Healthbox, Blue Cross Blue Shield of Massachusetts

Full Description: ABOUT US Our story is simple. In early 2020, the world was faced with an unprecedented pandemic, leaving many people feeling powerless.  We wanted to design a digital community that gave a sense of security back to our friends and loved ones. Armed with our exceptional technology, SafeSpaces helps millions around the world feel protected in an ever-changing environment. Our app is designed to stay one step ahead of your plans, and help stop the risk of exposing yourself and others to potential health and safety risks. So come and join us in leading the conversation towards a safer future, where establishments can feel proud of their efforts, and users can feel empowered in their contribution. Together, we can turn an unfortunate situation into a connected, healthier, safer space.  FOR OUR USERS Members of the community deserve to be informed. That’s where SafeSpaces comes in. From neighborhood parks, date-night restaurants, to even your workplace, our passion is making sure that every community can support one another. We strongly believe that people should feel empowered to keep each other accountable. And we want to make that as easy as possible.  When everyone does their part, the future becomes brighter for everyone. FOR ESTABLISHMENTS In the “new normal” of the post-pandemic life, an establishment’s commitment to maintaining health and safety standards is paramount to its success. The perception that a location is unclean can be devastating for a small business. SafeSpaces allows business owners to navigate through uneasy public perception. Establishments get an in depth understanding of how their current health and safety precautions are observed by the community, and can make any needed adjustments to promote the wellbeing of their patrons.
